### Meaning
### "Wind speed's association with slower elite times was directionally consistent across specifications (OLS, course-clustered, and Newey-West standard errors) for both sexes, but did not reach conventional significance in any version (p ranging 0.06–0.21). Combined with the confounding demonstrated in the unadjusted analysis — where wind's raw correlation with women's times was significant but attributable to course-level confounding with Boston — this suggests wind speed, as measured here (a single-point average without headwind/tailwind direction), is at most a modest factor in elite marathon performance, and this dataset lacks the power or precision to detect it conclusively."